'''Sergio Gabriel Martínez''' (born 21 February 1975 in [[Avellaneda]], [[Buenos Aires Province|Buenos Aires]], [[Argentina]]) is an [[Argentina|Argentine]] professional [[Boxing|boxer]].  He is the current  [[Lineal championship|Lineal]], [[The Ring (magazine)|''The Ring'']], and [[World Boxing Council|WBC]] [[middleweight]] champion.&amp;lt;ref&amp;gt;{{cite web|url=<a href="http://ringtv.craveonline.com/ratings/">http://ringtv.craveonline.com/ratings/</a> |title=Boxing Ratings &amp;amp;#124; RingTV |publisher=Ringtv.craveonline.com |date=2011-11-07 |accessdate=2011-11-13}}&amp;lt;/ref&amp;gt;&amp;lt;ref&amp;gt;{{cite web|url=<a href="http://boxrec.com/title_search.php?title=WBC&amp;amp;division=Middleweight&amp;amp;SUBMIT=Go">http://boxrec.com/title_search.php?title=WBC&amp;amp;division=Middleweight&amp;amp;SUBMIT=Go</a> |title=BoxRec Boxing Records |publisher=Boxrec.com |date= |accessdate=2011-11-13}}&amp;lt;/ref&amp;gt;&amp;lt;ref&amp;gt;{{cite web|url=<a href="http://boxrec.com/title_search.php?title=WBO&amp;amp;division=Middleweight&amp;amp;SUBMIT=Go">http://boxrec.com/title_search.php?title=WBO&amp;amp;division=Middleweight&amp;amp;SUBMIT=Go</a> |title=BoxRec Boxing Records |publisher=Boxrec.com |date= |accessdate=2011-11-13}}&amp;lt;/ref&amp;gt;&amp;lt;ref&amp;gt;{{cite web|url=<a href="http://wbcboxing.com/wbcVersEng/index.php?option=com_content&amp;amp;view=article&amp;amp;id=121%3Amedio&amp;amp;catid=15&amp;amp;Itemid=12">http://wbcboxing.com/wbcVersEng/index.php?option=com_content&amp;amp;view=article&amp;amp;id=121%3Amedio&amp;amp;catid=15&amp;amp;Itemid=12</a> |title=Middleweight |publisher=Wbcboxing.com |date=2011-06-04 |accessdate=2011-11-13}}&amp;lt;/ref&amp;gt; 

Martinez was previously in the [[light-middleweight]] division, where he held the [[World Boxing Council|WBC]] light-middleweight title (Interim then elevated to full status champion), as well as the [[World Boxing Council|WBC Latino]] title.&amp;lt;ref&amp;gt;{{cite web|url=<a href="http://boxrec.com/title_search.php?title=WBCLAT&amp;amp;division=Light%20Middleweight&amp;amp;SUBMIT=Go">http://boxrec.com/title_search.php?title=WBCLAT&amp;amp;division=Light%20Middleweight&amp;amp;SUBMIT=Go</a> |title=BoxRec Boxing Records |publisher=Boxrec.com |date= |accessdate=2011-11-13}}&amp;lt;/ref&amp;gt;&amp;lt;ref&amp;gt;{{cite web|url=<a href="http://boxrec.com/title_search.php?title=WBC&amp;amp;division=Light%20Middleweight&amp;amp;SUBMIT=Go">http://boxrec.com/title_search.php?title=WBC&amp;amp;division=Light%20Middleweight&amp;amp;SUBMIT=Go</a> |title=BoxRec Boxing Records |publisher=Boxrec.com |date= |accessdate=2011-11-14}}&amp;lt;/ref&amp;gt; Also, he has competed in the [[welterweight]] division, where he held the [[World Boxing Organization|WBO Latino]] title.&amp;lt;ref&amp;gt;{{cite web|url=<a href="http://boxrec.com/title_search.php?title=WBOLAT&amp;amp;division=Welterweight&amp;amp;SUBMIT=Go">http://boxrec.com/title_search.php?title=WBOLAT&amp;amp;division=Welterweight&amp;amp;SUBMIT=Go</a> |title=BoxRec Boxing Records |publisher=Boxrec.com |date= |accessdate=2011-11-14}}&amp;lt;/ref&amp;gt;

Martínez is currently rated as the number four [[pound for pound]] best boxer in the world by most sporting news and boxing websites, including [[Sports Illustrated]], [[ESPN]] and [[Yahoo! Sports]]. He is rated as the [[Ring Magazine pound for pound|no.4 pound for pound boxer in the world]] by [[The Ring (magazine)|The Ring]].&amp;lt;ref&amp;gt;{{cite web|last=Iole |first=Kevin |url=<a href="http://sports.yahoo.com/box/news;_ylt=Agb5zRlQDI76VGWKp9zwfB6UxLYF?slug=ki-iole_boxing_rankings_heavyweights_emerge_051711">http://sports.yahoo.com/box/news;_ylt=Agb5zRlQDI76VGWKp9zwfB6UxLYF?slug=ki-iole_boxing_rankings_heavyweights_emerge_051711</a> |title=Rankings: Heavyweight isn't deadweight – Boxing – Yahoo! Sports |publisher=Sports.yahoo.com |date= |accessdate=2011-11-14}}&amp;lt;/ref&amp;gt; In 2010 he received [[Ring Magazine Fighter of the Year|''The Ring'']] and [[Edward J. Neil Trophy|BWAA]] &amp;quot;Fighter of the Year&amp;quot; and ''The Ring'' [[Ring Magazine knockouts of the year|&amp;quot;Knockout of the Year&amp;quot;]] awards, resp. Martinez holds notable victories over former world champions [[Kelly Pavlik]], [[Paul Williams (boxer)|Paul Williams]], [[Sergiy Dzinziruk]] and [[Julio César Chávez, Jr.]].<span style="color:blue;">&lt;/rev&gt;</span>
